HAROLD MC MILLAN BIXBY
BOLTON LANDING. N. Y
Oct. 5th
Dear Emmy Lu:
Yours of the lst.
I have
advised the Foundation that I shall not
attend the meeting in Omaha in November.
Do you think you might
perhaps build
small fire under our Tallahassee politicos by
send-
ing then the agenda for the Omaha meeting withthe suggestion
that
they may perhaps miss the bus by reason of their activity on the
do nothing
frontier.
I think Evans might be the one to call the
Governor's attention to the fact
that the Darling Foundation tired
of waiting for action in Florida is turning its attention
toward
the Lewis and Clark promotion.
I frankly do not know whether or
not that would do any good.
Debby and I have postponed our trip and now plan on going down to
New York on or about the 21st
as I
have a meeting to attend on the
23rd.
I had hoped to spend a little time in N.Y.
but apart from the
meeting on
the 23rd there is nothing
to keep me there.
Could you
conveniently set up the meeting in Tallahassee for a day or two
than the 25th date that you suggest in your letter?
the 25th if I have to but would prefer a few days later.
In any event Debby will
stay on in N.Y. while I go on to Tallahassee
Captiva.
We are having our
car driven down so we are quite flex-
ible.
Tried
to phone you tonight but
no answer.
Guess this letter will do
as well because we have
If you should wish
me our number is Bolton Landing NH 4 9765.
Remember that I can be
in Tallahassee on the 25th if
required and I quite agree
that we can
something if we meet
there in force.
In fact I do not
believe a darn thing will happen unless and until we do.
Give Mary and Dick my very best when you see them.
Sincerely
Harold
